  "description": "Winter annual from Brassicaceae, native to southern Europe. Produces rosette of deeply pinnate, peppery leaves with watercress-like flavor; lacks the aquatic habitat requirement of watercress. Requires cool soil temperatures (\u003c70°F) to germinate. Exceptionally cold-hardy biennial in northern climates.",
